  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1982-03-02", 
    "text": "Productivity Incentive Act of 1982 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an income tax credit equal to five percent of the payments made by a taxpayer to an employee under a productivity incentive plan. Defines \"productivity incentive plan\" as a written plan which provides bonuses to employees resulting from increases in a company's productivity or cost-savings."
